Male . Temples with densely and rather finely punctate areas. Tergite 10 and sternite 9 of the male genital segment as in Figs. 77, 78 . Aedeagus (
Fig. 79
) large, narrow, 2.5 mm long, with short median lobe; parameres symmetrical; inner sac ribbon-like, covered with sparse little scales.

Distribution. This species occurs almost in all Africa south of the Sahara to Malawi and North Zimbabwe (
Fig. 64
).
